&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DIABETES SPECIALIST DIETITIAN &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Specialist Diabetes Dietitian 1.0wte Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for an exciting new post in the field of Adult Diabetes?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated team player with excellent time management skills to join our integrated Diabetes Team at the Hackney Diabetes service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a member of the highly regarded multidisciplinary diabetes service ,providing education to patients (and their carers, where applicable) in both individual and group settings, in both primary and secondary care. This post is for a Dietitian who has a passion and willingness to deliver excellent clinical knowledge of Diabetes into practice. We are based in the City &amp; Hackney area of inner London, which is a diverse and exciting place to work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a successful candidate you will possess excellent clinical reasoning skills, a balance of empathy and emotional resilience and advanced communication skills. We are committed to training, supervision and audit, to improve clinical skills and ensure a high quality service provision. You will take an active part in training Dietetic students and other staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Please note this role is 37.5 hours per week (flexible and there is also option of remote working)***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameVibhuti MistryJob titleTherapies Lead for Diabetes and Obesity and Joint Professional Lead for DieteticsEmail addressv.mistry1@nhs.netTelephone number0208 5105920 / 07584 544703Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vibhuti Mistry, Therapies Lead for Diabetes and Obesity and Joint Professional Lead for Dietetics, on email: v.mistry1@nhs.net or call 0208 5105920 / 07584 544703&lt;/p&gt;
